	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Wow, Futurlec seems to ROCK !!! I've never seen a site where searching for electronics composants is so confortable and with a so wide range of things available at very low price (not including shiping of course).
<br />
<br />Plus, they have SRAMs available with dual separate port. Imagine mapping such a SRAM on a cart on both $6000-$7fff on PRG bus, and $2000-$3ffff on CHR bus. You'd be able to effectivly write to CHRRAM during rendering !! Mapping it at $0000-$1fff would effectivly get 4 screen mirroring with the ability to write to all 4 nametables during rendering !! Awesome !
<br />
<br />EDIT : Okay, there is only up to 2k available, but that would do for two re-writable name tables (mirrored as usual), or just half a pattern table rewritable during rendering. Still sounds great.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
