	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have to agree with Memblers and Tokumaru on the Sivava programmer. I have it too, and I love it. Also, flash roms are easy to use and quick to program/erase.
<br />
<br />Now, when putting another rom on the board, I use CajoNES ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.zophar.net/utilities/nesutil.html">http://www.zophar.net/utilities/nesutil.html</a><!-- m --> ). It is a DOS program, but it makes it very easy to split the rom into PRG/CHR without the use of a hex editor. I believe F7 is the key to split roms into Pasofami format (PRG, CHR, and PRM). Don't worry about the PRM, but the PRG and CHR files will be ready to go.
<br />
<br />Good luck.
<br />
<br />NC

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


